[[Lieutenant-General]] '''Richard Friedrich Patrick Felton''' [[Order of the British Empire|CBE]] is the Director-General of the [[Defence Safety Authority]].

==Military career==
Felton was commissioned into the [[Royal Corps of Transport]] on 6 September 1985.<ref>{{London Gazette|issue=50398|supp=y|page=559|date=13 January 1986}}</ref> He became Commanding Officer of 9 Regiment Army Air Corps in April 2004, Chief of Staff of [[1st Armoured Division (United Kingdom)|1st (United Kingdom) Armoured Division]] in April 2007 and Commander of [[4th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters North East|4th Mechanized Brigade]] in January 2009.<ref name=bbc>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/8613389.stm|title=Brigadier Richard Felton takes over Task Force Helmand|date=10 April 2010|publisher=BBC|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> It was in this role that he was deployed as Commander of [[Task Force Helmand]] in April 2010.<ref name=bbc/> He went on to be Chief of Joint Forces Operations at [[Joint Forces Command|Joint Forces Headquarters]] in March 2011 and Commander of [[Joint Helicopter Command]] in March 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.defenceviewpoints.co.uk/defence-news/ups-and-outs-may-2013|title=Ups and outs|publisher=Defence News|date=May 2013|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> He became Director-General of the [[Defence Safety Authority]] in April 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gulabin.com/armynavy/pdf/Generals-Current.pdf|title=Generals: April 2017|accessdate=18 April 2017}}</ref>

